19.03	Apotemnophilia	Apotemnophilia	Apotemnophilia is a variety of Body Integrity Identity Disorder (BIID) in which otherwise sane and rational individuals express a strong and specific desire for the amputation of a healthy limb or limbs. Apotemnophilia has features in common with somatoparaphrenia. Some apotemnophiles seek surgeons to perform an amputation or purposefully injure a limb in order to force emergency medical amputation.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/3b/MRI_brain.jpg
